RESULTS: A total of 631 patients contributing 1282 SREs, were enrolled across 
Germany, Italy, Spain and the United Kingdom. Approximately a third of all SREs 
required an inpatient stay. Mean duration of inpatient stay for patients with 
SREs requiring one ranged from 8.4 to 41.1 days across all countries and SRE 
types.
CONCLUSION: All types of SREs are associated with substantial HRU burden. 
Preventing SREs by using the best therapeutic options available may help to 
reduce the burden to patients and healthcare systems.

